                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.88/1150</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T12:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Colonel Betancourt, advancing from Manzanillo toward Santiago had severe fight
                    yesterday afternoon at Bayamo where little loyal force was being besieged by
                    insurgents with two troops disloyal cavalry from Santiago. Federal forces after
                    two hours defeated insurgents who retreated by railroad toward Santiago. Three
                    federal wounded.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
